"title": "6604: acceptance, human",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6604: acceptance, human",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The response of human beings to the revelation and grace of God. It is seen in receiving Jesus Christ, his words and the message of the gospel, and in the acceptance of one another for his sake. Believers are called, too, to accept instruction and discipline and to submit to God's will for their lives.</p>\n<h2>Human beings are to accept Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Receiving Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12\">JHN 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:6\">COL 2:6</a></p>\n<h3>Accepting Jesus Christ by accepting others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:20\">JHN 13:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:40\">MAT 10:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:5\">MAT 18:5</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:37\">MRK 9:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:48\">LUK 9:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:16\">LUK 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:44\">JHN 12:44</a></p>\n<h3>Accepting Jesus Christ's words</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:8\">JHN 17:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:14\">MAT 11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:11-Matt19:12\">MAT 19:11–19:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:33-John3:34\">JHN 3:33–3:34</a></p>\n<h3>Refusing to accept Jesus Christ and his words</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:11\">JHN 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:11\">JHN 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:32\">JHN 3:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:43-John5:44\">JHN 5:43–5:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:60\">JHN 6:60</a></p>\n<h2>Acceptance of the gospel</h2>\n<h3>The gospel is worthy of acceptance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:15\">1TI 1:15</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:21\">JAS 1:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:23\">MAT 13:23</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:20\">MRK 4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:15\">LUK 8:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3\">1CO 15:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:9-1Tim4:10\">1TI 4:9–4:10</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of those accepting the gospel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:41\">ACT 2:41</a> <em>3,000 on the day of Pentecost</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:14\">ACT 8:14</a> <em>the Samaritans</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:1\">ACT 11:1</a> <em>the Gentiles</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:1\">1CO 15:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:4\">2CO 11:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:9\">GAL 1:9</a> <em>believers in Galatia</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:6\">1TH 1:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Rejection of the gospel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:18\">ACT 22:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:15\">ROM 11:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:14\">1CO 2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Acceptance of one another</h2>\n<h3>A right self-acceptance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:10\">1CO 15:10</a></strong> <em>Paul accepts himself as a sinner saved by God's grace and entrusted with an important ministry</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:14\">GAL 5:14</a></strong> <em>Loving others requires a proper self-love: the recognition that people are made in God's image and are the objects of his love.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:18\">LEV 19:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:39\">MAT 22:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:31\">MRK 12:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:33\">MRK 12:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:9\">ROM 13:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:12-1Tim1:14\">1TI 1:12–1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:8\">JAS 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Acceptance of one another because of God's example</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:7\">ROM 15:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:34\">JHN 13:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:12\">JHN 15:12</a></p>\n<h3>Acceptance of those whom God has accepted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:1\">ROM 14:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:18-Deut10:19\">DEU 10:18–10:19</a> <em>God's people should reflect his concern for the weak and defenceless</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:13-Matt19:14\">MAT 19:13–19:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:13-Mark10:14\">MRK 10:13–10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:15-Luke18:16\">LUK 18:15–18:16</a> <em>Jesus Christ rebukes his disciples for turning away children.</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:11-Acts9:17\">ACT 9:11–9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:12-Acts22:13\">ACT 22:12–22:13</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:27\">ACT 9:27</a> <em>Barnabas' acceptance of Saul</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:15\">ACT 10:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:28\">ACT 10:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:47\">ACT 10:47</a></p>\n<h3>Acceptance of outsiders who join God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:33-Lev19:34\">LEV 19:33–19:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:22-Ezek47:23\">EZK 47:22–47:23</a></p>\n<h3>Acceptance of itinerant ministers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:14\">GAL 4:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:10-1Cor16:11\">1CO 16:10–16:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:29-Phil2:30\">PHP 2:29–2:30</a></p>\n<h2>Acceptance of things given</h2>\n<h3>Acceptance of gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:35\">1SA 25:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen33:10-Gen33:11\">GEN 33:10–33:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:4\">1SA 10:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:3-1Tim4:4\">1TI 4:3–4:4</a></p>\n<h3>Refusal to accept gifts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:23-Gen14:24\">GEN 14:23–14:24</a> <em>Abraham refuses gifts offered by the king of Sodom</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:15-2Kgs5:16\">2KI 5:15–5:16</a> <em>Elisha refuses a gift offered by Naaman</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:4\">EST 4:4</a> <em>Mordecai refuses fine clothes from Esther.</em></p>\n<h2>Acceptance of instruction</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:22\">JOB 22:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:10\">PRO 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:8\">PRO 10:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:20\">PRO 19:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:24\">ISA 29:24</a></p>\n<h2>Acceptance of discipline</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:17\">JOB 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:18\">DEU 21:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:12\">PSA 94:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:11-Prov3:12\">PRO 3:11–3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:17\">PRO 10:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:5-Heb12:7\">HEB 12:5–12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:19\">REV 3:19</a></p>\n<h2>Acceptance of God's will</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:10\">JOB 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:8\">PSA 40:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:5\">ISA 50:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:28\">ROM 8:28</a></p>\n<h2>Acceptance of bribes forbidden</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:8\">EXO 23:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:17\">DEU 10:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:7\">2CH 19:7</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps15:5\">PSA 15:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:23\">PRO 17:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:15\">ISA 33:15</a></p>",
